I doubt that other powers (especially Great Britain) are going to allow
Russia to become this powerful in the Pacific.  I once wrote that "I have
toyed with the idea of the Russians succeeeding in establishing a lasting
protectorate in Kauai, if not all the islands, but finally gave it up
as implausible--too many other powers had greater interests in the
islands."  However, I do sympathize with the spirit of Mike Cleven's reply
at http://groups.google.com/group/soc.history.what-if/msg/7e850f63dd0002f5
"The prospect of a Hawaiian-Russian pidgin strikes me as very
interesting; I'll leave the geopolitics for later..."

