The thing to remember in Hawaii is the kings were very susceptible to
flattery, and a Russian Hawaiian partnership in getting all of the tea
(and china) out of China might have had more impact than all the
English visits by the royalty. The trick of the Hawaiian kings and
queens was staying alive in an atmosphere of Western diseases. Would
the Russians have carried fewer?

