Forgot, the Russians have an existing base in the Pacific in Alaska, a
source of wealth in the otter and had established friendship with the
Spanish Californios to the extent that if Rezanov had lived he would
have been in effective charge of Northern California from about 1810
on. Gold had been discovered by then but not publicized, if Alta
California is Russian California the Mexican war might end with the
United States getting their railroad into San Diego but not much else.
